    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
            <h5 class="text-muted">A little bit about me</h5>
            <p>
                My postdoc years I spent at the <wiki key="bu.math" /> at <wiki key="bu" />&mdash;a most amazing place in every respect&mdash;where in addition to the usual stuff I fell in love with topology.
            </p>
            <p>
                Previously, I graduated from the <wiki key="usc.math" /> at <wiki key="usc" /> in 2014 under the supervision of Prof. <wiki key="tartakov" />.
            </p>
            <p>
                And it all started with <wiki key="mipt" /> where I received my M.S. in Applied Mathematics and Physics / Information Processing and Control Systems in 2008. I still consider myself a bit of a physist.
            </p>
            <p>
                I will finish off with my favorite quote which I discovered <s>not so long</s> while watching one of the <wiki key="periodic.videos" /> about <wiki key="exploding.h.bubbles" />:
            </p>
            <div class="card-body">
                <blockquote class="blockquote mb-0" cite="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d49TzVF1gmY&t=203">
                    <p class="h6"><em>And it's always good to be wrong. It shows that you are learning something.</em></p>
                    <footer class="h6 mt-1">&mdash; <wiki key="poliakoff" /></footer>
                </blockquote>
                @*<blockquote class="blockquote mb-0" cite="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1HM_YBEfEDA&t=238">
